Rolled Sugar Cookies
Judy and Lauren Heumann

3/4 cup (150g) margarine
1 cup sugar
1 egg
1 tsp vanilla
2 1/2 cups flour
1 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp salt

Cream together margarine and sugar.  Beat in egg and vanilla.  Then mix in flour, baking powder, and salt.  Mix well.  Chill dough for at least an hour, covered.  Roll dough on a lightly floured board.  Cut with cookie cutters, bake at 350F for 8-10 minutes or until lightly browned.

Icing:

1/3 cup margarine, softened
1 cup powdered sugar (recipe says 3)
1 1/2 tsp vanilla
2 tbsp evaporated milk

Mix margarine and sugar well.  Add vanilla and beat until smooth.  Add food coloring.
